title.narrative: 201 MATERNAL, NEWBORN CHILD AND ADOLESCENT HEALTH

description.narrative: COs and partners supported by ROSA to improve maternal, newborn, child and adolescent health in South Asia to deliver high quality care and increase demand for high-impact interventions including Prevention of Mother to Child Transmission of HIV (PMTCT) and behaviours that save lives, particularly among vulnerable populations., which contributes to Child Health, Child Health (Covid), Maternal And Newborn Health, Maternal And Newborn Health (Covid), Technical Excellence In Policy And Programmes, Technical Excellence In Policy And Programmes (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Comprehensive, sustainable and enabling environment that leaves no child behind is supported by policies, programmes, strategies, budgets and actions of Governments, regional institutions, private sector, media, financial institutions, UN and UNICEF country programmes in South Asia, in development and humanitarian contexts.
